        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:58PM EDT by NWS Gray ME</headline>
        <description>At 658 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hartland Four Corners, or near White River Junction, moving east at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lebanon, Enfield, Sunapee, Cornish, Croydon, Plainfield, Grantham,
Springfield, Canaan, Newport, and Grafton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
